en: The Name of the column. Usually the value of the first row in the column.
fr: The Name of the column. Usually the value of the first row in the column.

en: A human readable Title for the column.
fr: A human readable Title for the column.

en: A Description of the column
fr: A Description of the column

en: Choose a Type for the data in the column
fr: Choose a Type for the data in the column

en: Choose the Format for the Type of data
fr: Choose the Format for the Type of data

en: Set a RDF Type to provide extra meaning to the Type
fr: Set a RDF Type to provide extra meaning to the Type

en: Set a Constraint to limit valid values
fr: Set a Constraint to limit valid values

en: Value(s) that indicate a Missing Value. Separate values with a comma.
fr: Value(s) that indicate a Missing Value. Separate values with a comma.

en: The Nameof the Table. Lower case, numbers, ".", "_", "-" characters only
fr: The Nameof the Table. Lower case, numbers, ".", "_", "-" characters only

en: The Title or one sentence description for this Table
fr: The Title or one sentence description for this Table

en: A Description for the Table
fr: A Description for the Table

en: The Sources for the data in this Table. Each Source MUST have a title and MAY have path and/or email address.
fr: The Sources for the data in this Table. Each Source MUST have a title and MAY have path and/or email address.

en: The Open License under which the Table is provided
fr: The Open License under which the Table is provided

en: Select the CSV Dialect for the Table
fr: Select the CSV Dialect for the Table

en: Select the column(s) that are the Primary Key that uniquely identifies each row in the table.
fr: Select the column(s) that are the Primary Key that uniquely identifies each row in the table.

en: Select the table to reference for the Foreign Key
fr: Select the table to reference for the Foreign Key

en: Select the column(s) that make up the Foreign Key Table
fr: Select the column(s) that make up the Foreign Key Table

en: The Name of the Data Package. Lower case, numbers, ".", "_", "-" characters only
fr: The Name of the Data Package. Lower case, numbers, ".", "_", "-" characters only

en: A globally unique identifier (Id) e.g. a UUID or DOI
fr: A globally unique identifier (Id) e.g. a UUID or DOI

en: The Open License under which the Data Package is provided
fr: The Open License under which the Data Package is provided

en: A Title or one sentence description for this Data Package
fr: A Title or one sentence description for this Data Package

en: The first paragraph of the Description should be usable as summary information for the package. Markdown formatting allowed.
fr: The first paragraph of the Description should be usable as summary information for the package. Markdown formatting allowed.

en: The Home Page
fr: The Home Page

en: The Version of the data package. It should conform to the [Data Package Version Pattern](http://frictionlessdata.io/specs/patterns/#data-package-version).
fr: The Version of the data package. It should conform to the [Data Package Version Pattern](http://frictionlessdata.io/specs/patterns/#data-package-version).

en: A list of Sources for this Data Package. Each Source MUST have a title and MAY have path and/or email address.
fr: A list of Sources for this Data Package. Each Source MUST have a title and MAY have path and/or email address.

en: A list of Contributors (people or organisations) who contributed to this Data Package
fr: A list of Contributors (people or organisations) who contributed to this Data Package

en: A list of Keywords to assist users searching for the package in catalogs
fr: A list of Keywords to assist users searching for the package in catalogs

en: The URL of an Image to use for this Data Package.
fr: The URL of an Image to use for this Data Package.
